resentation in art accompanied by a lamb. The colloquial form <i>Annes</i> led to some confusion with <i>Ann(e)</i> in earlier centuries. Frequent in the medieval period, the name was revived in the 19th century, and has been especially popular in Scotland.  See also  Annis ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705195,"age":22,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"When Agnes Brancestre was born about 1360, in Oxfordshire, England, her father, John Brancestre, was 47 and her mother, Margaret Mile, was 31. She married Richard d'Anvers II in 1389, in Oxfordshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died about 1395, in her hometown, at the age of 37, and was buried in Oxfordshire, England."},"et":{"about 1360–about 1395":"umbes 1360–umbes 1395","1348–1391":"1348–1391","1348–Male":"1348–Surnud","1352–Male":"1352–Surnud","1359–1395":"1359–1395","1360–1395":"1360–1395","1330–1409":"1330–1409","1382–1448":"1382–1448","1315–1392":"1315–1392","1330–1392":"1330–1392","about 1360":"umbes 1360","1330":"1330","1352":"1352","1395":"1395","1382":"1382","1360":"1360","1392":"1392","1391":"1391","1448":"1448","1315":"1315","1359":"1359","1348":"1348","Bef 1392":"enne 1392","1389":"1389","1409":"1409","about 1395":"umbes 1395","Colthorpe, Oxfordshire, England":"Colthorpe, Oxfordshire, England","Cropredy Church, Oxfordshire, England":"Oxfordshire, England","Banbury, Oxfordshire, England":"Banbury, Oxfordshire, England","Oxfordshire, England":"Oxfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Ipswell, Oxfordshire, England":"Oxfordshire, England","Donc